sec.p:
Phenotypic plasticity is a central concept in evolutionary ecology (
  Schlichting 1986; 
  Scheiner 1993; 
  Schlichting and Pigliucci 1998). The seminal work of 
  Weis and Gorman (1990) has clarified that quantification of natural selection on the level of the reaction norm is pivotal in understanding the evolution of plasticity. From this perspective, repeated observations on long-lived organisms under natural conditions in combination with the methodology we here presented constitute a powerful approach to quantify variation in the reaction-norm properties and linking them to variation in fitness.
